&lt;h2 id="duration-format">Duration format&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Flags that take durations must end with &lt;strong>&lt;code>d&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>, &lt;strong>&lt;code>h&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>, &lt;strong>&lt;code>m&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>, or &lt;strong>&lt;code>s&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>, with a digit before the suffix (validated at startup).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Configuration files</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/deployment/configuration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/deployment/configuration/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="remote-store-store_configyaml">Remote store (&lt;code>store_config.yaml&lt;/code>)&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nt">remote_store&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">provider&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;minio&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">bucket&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;bkt1&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">access_key&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;minioadmin&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">secret_key&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;minioadmin&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">create_bucket_on_empty&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="kc">true&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">endpoint&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;minio:9000&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">./logsGo --store-config-path&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>store_config.yaml
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="queue-queue-configyaml">Queue (&lt;code>queue-config.yaml&lt;/code>)&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nt">queue&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">url&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">amqp://guest:guest@rabbitmq:5672/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">name&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">logs&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">numWorkers&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="m">4&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">./logsGo --queue-config-path&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>queue-config.yaml
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="tls">TLS&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>See &lt;code>examples/tls-config.yaml&lt;/code> for cert and key path fields. Enable with:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Go client library</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/guides/client-library/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/guides/client-library/</guid><description>&lt;p>Module path:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">github.com/Saumya40-codes/LogsGO/client/go/logclient
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="connect-insecure">Connect (insecure)&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nx">c&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">err&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">:=&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">logclient&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nf">NewLogClient&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">ctx&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;localhost:50051&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">)&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Default gRPC address in the server is &lt;code>:50051&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="connect-with-tls">Connect with TLS&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Use &lt;code>NewLogClientWithTLS(ctx, addr, tlsConfig)&lt;/code> when the server is started with &lt;code>--tls-config-path&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="queue-aware-client">Queue-aware client&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nx">c&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">err&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">:=&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">logclient&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nf">NewLogClientWithQueue&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">ctx&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">grpcAddr&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">&amp;amp;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">logclient&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">QueueOpts&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">{&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="nx">QueueName&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;logs&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="nx">Url&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;amqp://guest:guest@localhost:5672/&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">},&lt;/span> &lt;span class="kc">true&lt;/span> &lt;span class="cm">/* insecure gRPC */&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="kc">nil&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">)&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Publishing to the queue decouples your app from LogsGo ingest latency.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Storage tiers</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/storage/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/storage/</guid><description>&lt;p>LogsGo keeps writes simple and retention multi-tiered. Each tier optimizes for a different access pattern.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="1-in-memory-store">1. In-memory store&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Backed by a &lt;strong>skiplist&lt;/strong> for O(log n) insertion and query.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Ideal for &lt;strong>hot&lt;/strong> data and low-latency instant queries.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Eviction / flush driven by:
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;code>--max-time-in-mem&lt;/code> (default &lt;code>1h&lt;/code>)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;code>--max-logs-in-mem&lt;/code> (default &lt;code>10000&lt;/code>)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="2-local-store-badgerdb">2. Local store (BadgerDB)&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Persistent &lt;strong>on-disk&lt;/strong> store under &lt;code>--data-dir&lt;/code> (default &lt;code>./data&lt;/code>).&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Receives flushed memory segments.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Use &lt;code>--unlock-data-dir&lt;/code> only if you understand multi-process access risks (not recommended for production).&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="3-cloud--bucket-store">3. Cloud / bucket store&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Configure an S3-compatible backend (AWS S3, MinIO, etc.) via YAML:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Query language (LogsGoQL)</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/query-language/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/query-language/</guid><description>&lt;p>LogsGo ships a small, focused query language for filtering log series. Expressions are used from the &lt;strong>dashboard&lt;/strong> and the &lt;strong>REST&lt;/strong> &lt;code>expression&lt;/code> parameter.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="grammar-ebnf">Grammar (EBNF)&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">query -&amp;gt; expr
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">expr -&amp;gt; term (OR term)*
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">term -&amp;gt; factor (AND factor)*
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">factor -&amp;gt; &amp;#34;(&amp;#34; expr &amp;#34;)&amp;#34; | comparison
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">comparison -&amp;gt; ident operator value
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">ident -&amp;gt; level | service | message | &amp;lt;custom label keys&amp;gt;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">operator -&amp;gt; &amp;#34;=&amp;#34; | CONTAINS
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">value -&amp;gt; string | ident
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>In the UI / HTTP API, &lt;strong>AND&lt;/strong> is often written as &lt;code>&amp;amp;&lt;/code> and &lt;strong>OR&lt;/strong> as &lt;code>|&lt;/code> in compact form:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Query execution</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/query-execution/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/query-execution/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="execution-plan">Execution plan&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The LogsGoQL engine &lt;strong>parses&lt;/strong> the expression into an AST, then builds a &lt;strong>query plan&lt;/strong>. Each store executes the plan (or relevant slices) and results are &lt;strong>merged&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/images/query-execution.png" alt="Query execution plan">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Message queue ingestion</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/queueing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/queueing/</guid><description>&lt;p>For peak throughput or producer/consumer decoupling, LogsGo can ingest from &lt;strong>RabbitMQ&lt;/strong>. Producers enqueue batches; &lt;strong>N workers&lt;/strong> on the LogsGo side consume in &lt;strong>round-robin&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/images/logs-queueing.png" alt="Queueing model">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;em>Ideal queueing model&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="server-configuration">Server configuration&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Create a queue config file and pass &lt;code>--queue-config-path&lt;/code>:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Authentication &amp; TLS</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/authentication/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/authentication/</guid><description>&lt;p>Security features are &lt;strong>opt-in&lt;/strong> via CLI flags and small config files.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/images/auth_in_logsGo.png" alt="Auth flow">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;em>Authentication design notes&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="jwt-authentication">JWT authentication&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>If &lt;code>--public-key-path&lt;/code> points at an &lt;strong>RSA public key&lt;/strong> file, LogsGo enables JWT validation for &lt;strong>gRPC and HTTP&lt;/strong> servers.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Benchmarks</title><link>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/benchmarks/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saumya40-codes.github.io/LogsGO/docs/benchmarks/</guid><description>&lt;p>Benchmarks live under &lt;a href="https://github.com/Saumya40-codes/LogsGO/tree/main/bench">&lt;code>/bench&lt;/code>&lt;/a> in the repository (docker-compose driven load tests).&lt;/p>
